&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Summary: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;It is our purpose to provide World Class GIS solutions that exceed our Member’s expectations. This will be done through the building and maintenance of our Member’s GIS databases using NISC&#39;s proprietary Mapping GIS solution as well as other GIS solutions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:278}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Essential Duties: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;1&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;multilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Setup, edit and maintain GIS datasets for Members including, but not limited to; layers, fields, domains, geometric networks, and associated attributes and assets.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;1&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;multilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Perform quality assurance including; collecting and analyzing database updates and work orders to ensure “as-built” conversion process is successful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li

&lt;p&gt;NISC develops and implements enterprise-level and customer-facing software solutions for over 960+ energy cooperatives and communication organizations across North America. Our mission is to deliver technology solutions and services that are Member-focused, quality-driven and valued-priced. We exist to serve our Members and help them serve their communities through our innovative software products, services and outstanding customer support. We are an AI-forward company committed to being a technology leader in our industry. NISC has been ranked in ComputerWorld’s Best Places to Work for 23 years, and we are looking for qualified individuals to join our team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NISC is looking to fill a position working with our Operations – Asset &amp;amp; Ticket Management products. &amp;nbsp;You will be responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementing the plant records and trouble ticketing applications within iVUE. Also responsible for implementing the Operations – Asset &amp;amp; Ticket Management applications such as our mobile solutions, scheduling tools, and open API&#39;s. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will work with the Member/customer to effectively implement the applications. This includes working as a project manager to manage project timelines, communicating with internal and external individuals of project expectations, and configuring the application via creating or modifying the necessary interface code and applications options. It also includes analyzing the data from the member/customer’s current system to ensure that it is properly converted into the NISC software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Schedule: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid (after an initial training period) from one of the office locations listed below:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cedar Rapids, IA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mandan, ND &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid Schedule: Minimum of working 3 days per week in the office and ability to work up to all 5 days a week in the office, as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Required Days from an Office Location: Tuesday and Wednesday - the third required day will be up to the candidate and their supervisor to choose&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides superior customer support to internal and external customers in all encounters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct implementation analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in features and functionality in software and oversee resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follows all established software implementation methodologies and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs quality testing as it relates to system integration dependent on the tasks assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and complete implementation documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilizes all implementation best practices and artifacts for all implementation projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists customers in all aspects of implementation including troubleshooting, training, and on-going support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Job Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years Telecom/Broadband experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of Excel and other MS Office products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer orientation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent research and problem-solving skills with a strong attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written interpersonal and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to organize and prioritize.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, as well as in a team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to interact in a positive manner with internal and external contacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Application Program

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;NISC develops and implements enterprise-level and customer-facing software solutions for over 960+ utilities and broadbands across North America. Our mission is to deliver technology solutions and services that are Member-focused, quality driven and valued priced. We exist to serve our Members and help them serve their communities through our innovative software products, services and outstanding customer support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;About this Job:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;The primary focus of this position is to provide virtual and onsite Business Process Consultation and training services for the business processes supported by NISC’s Mapping/Staking solutions. Strong industry experience is a must, and experience with GIS Systems is a plus. Experience with other NISC system integrations is also beneficial, though not a requirement. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position resides in the Member Value team within the Member Success division, and works closely with an enterprise team of Member Value Consultants and the Account Management team. The mission of the position is to enhance the success of Members and other NISC employees through providing expertise and guidance on industry and solution best practices. The team continues to evolve in how NISC can more effectively add value to Members, so a person with strong initiative and an innovative mindset is the right fit for this team. This position is expected to travel onsite to Member locations up to 6 engagements per year. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;What you will do as the Member Value Consultant:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;1&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;multilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Provide remote and onsite consulting and implementation services to members around product utilization and best practices.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
